# Class: obo:UBERON_0001485 (knee joint)

AnnotationAssertion(Annotation(oboInOwl:hasDbXref "Wikipedia:Knee") obo:IAO_0000115 obo:UBERON_0001485 "The knee joint joins the thigh with the leg and consists of two articulations: one between the femur and tibia, and one between the femur and patella. It is the largest and most complicated joint in the human body. The knee is a mobile trocho-ginglymus (i.e. a pivotal hinge joint), which permits flexion and extension as well as a slight medial and lateral rotation[WP,unvetted].")
